Ask HN: Open license, but not for AI model training
text:
Hello HN!

I like probably most of you put a lot of code up on GitHub. With the advent of copilot, I have been growing a little bit uneasy about the software that I write being used for training purposes. I generally like releasing my code under an open license, but I would rather the consumer of my software be humans rather than an algorithm.

Is there a variant of the GPL or the MIT license that prohibits using code as part of a big corporate training set?

With that said, I am planning on moving most of my code over to SourceHut, as I like the overall philosophy a lot.
